The Governor of Ekiti State, Dr. Kayode Fayemi, on Sunday revealed that the state has recorded three new cases of COVID 19. With these new cases, Ekiti now has ten patients in its isolation centre. Fayemi, who broke the news in a tweet on his Twitter handle, on Sunday, said there was a need for residents to be cautious about the scourge with the new development. “We got information from NCDC tonight that three more persons tested positive for COVID-19 disease. “Two are contacts of the medical doctor still in our care and another person who sneaked into the state before he was quarantined. “This underscores the need for extra vigilance. ” Meanwhile, the State Commissioner for Health, Dr. Mojisola Yaya-Kolade at a COVID-19 press conference said all the patients in the isolation centre are stable and responding to treatment. Yaya -Kolade revealed the intention of the government to provide a COVID 19 testing laboratory in the state to buoy the testing capacity of the state. The Commissioner also announced that all the corpses to be buried in Ekiti must get approval and a certificate of clearance as part of strategies to tame the spread of the disease. Ekiti govt set to establish own COVID-19 testing laboratory Unconscious third COVID-19 patient in Ekiti stabilised, 70 isolated - Health Commissioner Katsina resident tests positive for COVID-19 in Ekiti